HEADWORD: Cotangent
<hw>Co*tan"gent</hw> <pr>(k?-t?n"j<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[For <ets>co</ets>. <ets>tangens</ets>, an abbrev. of L.
<ets>complementi tangens</ets>. See <er>Tangent</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Trig.)</fld> <def>The tangent of the complement of an arc or
angle. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Functions</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cotarnine</ent>⟦br⟧
